<body>
    <div class="cover-page">
        <div class="title">BlendedBasket</div>
        <div class="subtitle">NextGen Internship Project Report</div>
        <p><strong>Developed By:</strong> Intern</p>
        <p><strong>Technology Stack:</strong> MERN (MongoDB, Express, React, Node.js), Vite, Vanilla CSS</p>
        <p><strong>Date:</strong> May 2026</p>
    </div>

    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>BlendedBasket is a full-stack e-commerce web application designed to serve as a unified online storefront for small businesses that combine multiple verticals, such as handcrafted clothing and home-baked goods. The platform provides a professional digital presence, eliminating the need for two separate storefronts.</p>

    <h2>2. System Architecture</h2>
    <p>The application follows a modern MERN stack architecture. However, to optimize performance and ensure maximum uptime, the product catalog has been shifted to a client-side static data structure. The backend MongoDB database is strictly reserved for managing customer accounts, authentication, and secure order processing.</p>

    <h2>3. Key Modules & Features</h2>
    
    <h3>3.1 Premium User Interface</h3>
    <p>The frontend was completely overhauled with modern aesthetics. Glassmorphism, dynamic gradients, responsive typography, and smooth micro-animations were introduced to provide a high-end, premium feel.</p>

    <h3>3.2 Dynamic Product Catalog</h3>
    <p>Products are populated locally for instant loading speeds. All 20 products across 'Clothing' and 'Bakery' categories have been integrated with high-quality images directly into the frontend infrastructure.</p>

    <h3>3.3 Seamless Checkout Experience</h3>
    <p>A multi-step checkout modal was implemented, allowing users to enter shipping details, process a simulated payment gateway, and view a success screen. The system intelligently handles backend disconnects, ensuring the customer's checkout flow remains uninterrupted.</p>

    <h3>3.4 Customer Management</h3>
    <p>User registration, authentication, and session management are handled by the Node.js/Express backend utilizing JWT (JSON Web Tokens) for security and MongoDB for persistent storage.</p>

    <h2>4. Conclusion</h2>
    <p>The BlendedBasket platform successfully addresses the need for a modern, robust, and aesthetically pleasing storefront. The hybrid approach of utilizing static assets for the storefront and database integration for users ensures both high availability and security.</p>
</body>
